<subSubSection pageId="189" pageNumber="468" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="189.[727,1318,1163,1586]" lastBlockId="189.[113,1317,1597,2022]" pageId="189" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[728,1007,1396,1429]" pageId="189" pageNumber="468">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 122-172 mm, tail 75-104 mm, ear 15-18 mm, hindfoot 24-29 mm; weight 36-125 g. See general characters of the genus under the Anazonian Hocicudo (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hershkovitz" authorityYear="1994" box="[1059,1254,1557,1586]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Oxymycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="189" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amazonicus">O. amazonicus</taxonomicName>
) account. Cook’s Hocicudo is a medium-sized species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1837" box="[894,1051,1597,1626]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Oxymycterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="189" pageNumber="468" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oxymycterus</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum pelage is reddish to dark brown and long in most specimens. Venter occasionally has white spots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
